 {"id":"beads_rust-vo6l","title":"[LOW] README command inventory omits implemented user-facing subcommands","description":"Root cause: README.md command table at README.md:388-449 documents only a subset of the public Clap command enum. The implementation exposes additional user-facing commands in src/cli/mod.rs:733-942 and main dispatch in src/main.rs:202-332: agents, audit, changelog, completions, defer, epic, graph, history, info, lint, orphans, query, schema, status, undefer, and where. Some are mentioned elsewhere, but the README Commands section presents itself as the command reference and leaves these discoverability gaps. Repro: compare README.md:388-449 with `RUST_LOG=error br --help` or src/cli/mod.rs:733-942. Proposed fix: either make README Commands explicitly a quick-start subset with a link to docs/CLI_REFERENCE.md, or add rows/sections for every implemented public subcommand and major nested command. Test to add: docs snapshot/check that README command inventory is either marked partial or contains every top-level Clap command except help/feature-gated commands.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cod_1","created_at":"2026-04-22T17:14:47.235676928Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T18:05:22.584303656Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T18:05:22.583962546Z","close_reason":"Updated README Commands inventory to include implemented top-level user-facing subcommands omitted from the table; verified against rch-wrapped cargo run -- --help and src/cli/mod.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":327,"issue_id":"beads_rust-vo6l","author":"cod_1","text":"degraded-coordination: files: README.md","created_at":"2026-04-22T17:59:47Z"}]}
 {"id":"beads_rust-vqmz","title":"Reject symlinked DB recovery before WAL quarantine","description":"Round-2 review found that symlinked beads.db recovery now refuses to rebuild the database path, but open_sqlite_storage_with_recovery_strategy still calls quarantine_truncated_wal_sidecar before the symlink rejection inside backup/cleanup. A symlinked beads.db with a truncated beads.db-wal can therefore create .br_recovery artifacts and move sidecars even though recovery should be a no-op refusal. Move the symlink guard ahead of pre-open sidecar quarantine and add regression coverage.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-21T18:21:00.931167361Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T18:27:30.043330254Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T18:27:30.042997851Z","close_reason":"Skipped truncated WAL quarantine for symlinked database paths and extended symlink recovery coverage so refusal leaves sidecars and targets untouched.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
